Resizing
-------------
variablename=cv.resize(imagename,dsize,interpolation)
small=cv.resize(img_rgb,(img_rgb.shape[1]//2,img_rgb.shape[0]//2),interpolation=cv.INTER_AREA)

- Changing the dimensions (width Ã— height) of an image.
- Adjust image to fit models, reduce storage, or improve performance.

Methods:

	- Downsampling: Reducing size (loses detail).
	- Upsampling: Increasing size (may introduce blur).





